## Conclusion

`MATERIAL_FIDELITY_GAP`

The R005 report correctly established that the exact original uncommitted-worktree reproduction for `AUDOBS-0003` was rejected after R004. It did not establish closure of the broader clean, committed, internally self-consistent replacement condition described in the original evidence.

The stronger R005 replacement harness created a duplicate `MANIFEST.sha256`, so verification failed before the Git-status binding was isolated. A clean committed replacement of the snapshot, `TARGET.json`, loose manifest, audit pack and sidecars was not successfully constructed and tested.

## Disposition by observation

- `AUDOBS-0011`: remediation remains supported for the tested `.env`, `.env.*` and extensionless-file classes. The phrase “exactly reproduces” in R005 is narrower than the actual setup because a standalone temporary directory was used instead of the original full repository copy. This is a wording/scope qualification, not evidence that the repair failed.
- `AUDOBS-0012`: remediation remains supported; the original oversized-file reporting condition was faithfully retested.
- `AUDOBS-0003`: interpret the R005 verdict as `PARTIAL_REMEDIATION_CONFIRMED`. The dirty-worktree variant is closed. The coherently committed whole-overlay replacement remained open at the time of R005.
- `AUDOBS-0010`, `AUDOBS-0014`, `AUDOBS-0015`, `AUDOBS-0016`: R005 preserved their original open status, limitations and non-claims.

## Required next test

Construct a valid replacement snapshot whose internal manifests and metadata are self-consistent, update `TARGET.json`, all loose manifests, the audit pack and sidecars, commit the complete replacement so `git status` is clean, and require `audit-check` to reject it by comparing the snapshot payload to the immutable Git tree named by `target_commit`.

## R006 response

R006 adds an independent payload-to-Git-tree binding and a regression that performs the required clean committed replacement test. Until R006 passes review and an external retest, `AUDOBS-0003` remains partially remediated rather than closed.

